%%{init: {'theme': 'default', 'sequence': {'actorFontSize': 22, 'actorFontWeight': 'bold', 'messageFontSize': 20, 'noteFontSize': 18, 'mirrorActors': false, 'actorMargin': 60, 'boxMargin': 12, 'messageMargin': 40, 'wrap': true}}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    actor RSU

    participant UI as nji-ui judge module
    participant Judge as nji-judge
    participant Itin as nji-itinerary
    participant Sit as nji-sitting

    rect rgb(232, 240, 250)
        Note over RSU,Sit: Phase 1 — Create judge profile
        RSU->>UI: open Manage Judges and click Create
        RSU->>UI: enter personal and role-specific details
        UI->>Judge: POST /v1/judges
        Judge->>Judge: validate per FR11
        Judge->>Judge: persist judge row
        Judge-->>UI: 201 judge
    end

    rect rgb(232, 250, 232)
        Note over RSU,Sit: Phase 2 — Define working pattern and jurisdictional split
        RSU->>UI: open Working Pattern tab, choose None / Daily / Weekly
        RSU->>UI: set target sit %, per-day work types, jurisdictional split
        UI->>Judge: POST /v1/judges/{id}/working-patterns
        Judge->>Judge: validate jurisdictional split sums to 100% per FR16
        Judge->>Judge: persist working pattern
    end

    rect rgb(250, 240, 230)
        Note over RSU,Sit: Phase 3 — Forward-sitting generation up to next 31 March per FR13
        Note right of Judge: Generation is in the same transaction as the pattern save. Prior absences on affected dates are preserved.
        Judge->>Judge: compute target dates up to next 31 March
        Judge->>Judge: skip dates with existing absences
        Judge->>Judge: persist planned sittings
        Judge->>Judge: commit transaction
        Judge-->>UI: 201 working pattern with generated sittings count
        UI-->>RSU: confirmation toast
    end

    Note over RSU,Sit: Downstream — nji-itinerary now sees the planned sittings via SQL JOIN, and nji-sitting picks them up for daily confirmation. See itinerary-federated-read.md and salaried-sitting-confirmation.md.
